org.shared.array.sparse

Class ProtoSparseArray<T extends ProtoSparseArray<T,V,E,D>,V,E,D extends Array<D,E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.shared.array.sparse.ProtoSparseArray<T,V,E,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the parameterization lower bounded by ProtoSparseArray itself.
    V - the storage array type.
    E - the element type.
    D - the dense array type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Array<T,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IntegerSparseArray, ObjectSparseArray, RealSparseArray

    public abstract class ProtoSparseArray<T extends ProtoSparseArray<T,V,E,D>,V,E,D extends Array<D,E>>
extends Object
implements Array<T,E>
    An abstract, primordial base class for all sparse arrays.
